HERE COMES A Merry Christmas

Up in Quebec they do it in grand style, firing a blazing wheel through the snow in honor of Christmas. A bit different, to be sure — but then, every country celebrates Christmas in its own way. And each of them has discovered that Canadian Club is one of the finest ways to say “Merry Christmas.”

1. Why ignite a crack o’ceer like this high in the hills of Quebec? Because it’s a tradition — and one of the gayest customs of all the Yule customs in Canada.

2. Having a formal highball with Christmas in England — a toast to Christmas with Canadian Club.

3. In Sweden you get into the rhythm of Christmas — and the custom of toasting good friends with a good drink... like Canadian Club.

So around the world the custom of Christmas is often the custom of Canadian Club. It's a whisky with a taste that people find extraordinary. People of experience — who know what to look for in fine whisky — always say, “Make mine Canadian Club.”
